selling airlines was not wrong but selling everything at the bottom was. he should have realized fed bail out money will help them short term. 

Buffet's greatest wins happened when money was not so easy and so he had cash when it was desperately needed. That does not look likely anymore. Plus he got good companies at very cheap valuation because of short term issues(Amex, Coco cola etc). Dont see that happening these days with so much money chasing yield everywhere. 

&amp;#x200B;

On top of it his reluctance to look at tech companies( I know Todd/Ted bought into Apple and recently Amazon) means he is missing it biggest disruptors going forward. That is why Berkshire has underformed S&amp;P for a long time now. 

&amp;#x200B;

That said Berkshire is still a good investment if you want to go contrary to conventional wisdom.
